# Outfitd User Persona Template

Copy this file to `user_persona.md` and fill it in with your own details.
This file is the single most important input to the system — the more specific you are,
the better Outfitd's recommendations will be.

`user_persona.md` is gitignored so your personal measurements stay local.

---

## 1. Biometrics & Measurements

*   **Height:** 5'11"
*   **Weight:** 175 lbs
*   **Chest:** 40"
*   **Natural Waist (Belly Button):** 32"
*   **Hip/Lower Waist (Belt Line):** 34"
*   **Thighs:** 21"
*   **Inseam:** 32"

## 2. Body Morphology & Fit Logic

**Top Half:**
*   *The Problem:* [Describe your specific fit challenge — e.g., "broad shoulders make the chest too tight in slim fits."]
*   *The Solution:* [What works — e.g., "Athletic fit or relaxed fit with a tapered waist."]
*   *Sizing:* **Medium (M)** across most brands.

**Bottom Half:**
*   *The Problem:* [Describe — e.g., "Slim jeans cut off circulation at the quads."]
*   *The Solution:* [e.g., "Athletic taper or high-stretch elastane blends."]
*   *Sizing:* **32x32**

## 3. Lifestyle & Use Case Context

*   **Location:** [Your city/region and climate — e.g., "Chicago, IL — cold winters, hot humid summers."]
*   **Work:** [e.g., "Hybrid office — 3 days in office, 2 WFH."]
*   **Wear Frequency:** [e.g., "'Going out' clothes worn 2-3x per week. Prioritize versatility over trend."]
*   **Budget:** Tops: ~$50–$80. Bottoms: ~$80–$130.

## 4. Style Preferences

*   **Preferred Tops:** [e.g., "T-shirts, henleys, and casual button-downs. No graphic tees."]
*   **Preferred Bottoms:** [e.g., "Dark denim, slim chinos, joggers for WFH."]
*   **Vibe:** [e.g., "Smart-casual, elevated basics, minimal/clean aesthetic."]

## 5. Color Palette

*   **Neutrals:** [e.g., "Black, White, Heather Grey, Charcoal."]
*   **Earth Tones:** [e.g., "Olive, Tan, Rust."]
*   **Accent:** [e.g., "Burgundy, Forest Green."]

## 6. Approved Brand Roster & Sizing

| Brand | Category | Preferred Model/Cut | Size | Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **[Brand]** | Tees | [Model name] | M | [Why it works for your body type] |
| **[Brand]** | Jeans | [Model name] | 32x32 | [e.g., "High stretch — accommodates athletic build."] |
